node BKZ · BKZ · ⟦THE BROTHERS KARAMAZOV:BKZ:6a3d0d⟧

WHO   — THE BROTHERS KARAMAZOV — a UD0 book-world
WHAT  — The Brothers Karamazov — Dostoevsky's summa: a murder mystery wrapped around the Grand Inquisitor and the problem of evil, answered by Alyosha, Zosima, and ‘Hurrah for Karamazov!’
WHERE — a Russian town, a monastery, and a courtroom, among a sensual father and his three (or four) sons  Framework inputs: the novel (1880, serialized in The Russian Messenger); the Book of Job; Schiller; Russian Orthodoxy; Dostoevsky's own faith and doubt  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Universe David 0)
WHY   — Because the novel asks the question of the age — if God is dead, is everything permitted? — builds the case against God more powerfully than for, and answers it not with logic but with a way of living: active love.
HOW   — Crystallized from the 1880 novel — the murder of the buffoon-father Fyodor Pavlovich, the trial of his son Dmitri, and beneath it the deepest argument ever staged between faith and atheism.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  He built the case against God so well it has never been refuted — and answered it not with an argument but with active love, and ‘Hurrah for Karamazov!’

